<style>
.row.courses-welcome {
  border: 1px solid #BBE5EE;
  padding: 1em;
  border-radius: 4px;
  background-color: #eff1f3;
  margin-bottom: 1em !important;
}
.courses-welcome-title {
  font-weight: 400;
  text-align: center;
}
.courses-welcome-instructions {
  text-indent: 1em;
  margin: 0.2em;
  font-size: 0.9em;
}
.custom-button.approve-courses {
  width: 100%;
  height: 3em;
  margin-top: 3em;
}
</style>

<div class="row courses-welcome">
  <div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
    <p class="courses-welcome-title">This is where you manage the courses that you want to tutor.</b> 
    <p class="courses-welcome-instructions">Use the select dropdowns to pick a subject and course and then enter the hourly rate you would like to charge for that particular course.</p>
    <p class="courses-welcome-instructions">You can enter different rates for different courses.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
    <p class="courses-welcome-instructions"> After adding a course, you can edit the hourly rate for that course or delete it entirely from your course list.</p>
    <p class="courses-welcome-instructions">You currently have only the one course you entered on the initial sign-up form in your course list. If you'd like to add more courses, you can do that now or come back later.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="small-12 large-4 columns">
    <p class="courses-welcome-instructions">Whether you want to start with one course or add more, click the "Approve Courses" button when you're finished adding your initial courses and are ready to start tutoring.</p>
    <%= form_for @tutor do |f| %>
      <%= f.hidden_field :courses_approved, value: true %>
      <%= f.submit "Approve Courses", class: 'custom-button approve-courses' %>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>